      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-001",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model credibly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for Class II CPB device",
      "description": "The validated CFD model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump is sufficiently credible to identify the worst-case hemolysis operating point across the five evaluated flow-speed combinations under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions. The relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by the model satisfies RH < 1 with respect to the predicate device benchmark, supporting the submission claim that the design meets the hemolysis acceptance criterion at Model Risk Level 2. This claim encompasses the full operating envelope of 2–6 L/min flow and 2500–4500 RPM speed combinations relevant to Class II CPB indications.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; 5 discrete flow-speed operating points; MRL 2 credibility requirements; Class II 510(k) submission context",
      "purpose": "Provide the primary credibility claim supporting regulatory acceptance of CFD hemolysis predictions as a substitute for additional physical bench testing under the stated COU"
    }
  ],
